Ambassador James Hormel, a remarkable individual, has passed away, leaving behind a legacy of kindness and commitment to human rights. He played a significant role in founding the Human Rights Campaign and advocating for those affected by HIV/AIDS, changing lives and inspiring future leaders. As the first openly gay ambassador of the United States, Jim represented the best of America and paved the way for others. The author expresses gratitude for Jim's friendship and guidance over the years and offers condolences to his husband, children, grandchildren, and great-grandchildren.